# fismen Caddy sites — synced from the live /etc/caddy/Caddyfile on 2026-06-12
# (Phase 1 of the migration; the earlier May copy had drifted). The global
# `{ admin 10.228.107.1:2019 }` block is lifted out: NixOS generates the
# global block from services.caddy.globalConfig — see caddy.nix.
#
# NOTES:
#   * `bind 100.86.115.86` lines hardcode fismen's CURRENT tailnet IP. On oink
#     (interim) they are rewritten via replaceStrings in
#     hosts/oink/fismen-interim.nix; after the reinstall, update them to the
#     NEW tailnet IP `tailscale up` hands out.
#   * The (cf) snippet needs the Caddy cloudflare-DNS plugin (caddy.nix builds
#     it) + CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN in the environment (sops → EnvironmentFile).
#   * `root * /var/www/<site>` static sites need those trees rsynced over.
#   * `reverse_proxy 10.228.107.x` targets require instances keeping their
#     IPs — pin each instance's ipv4.address on copy (see MIGRATION.md table).

# Cloudflare DNS-01 challenge (used by domains whose DNS lives in Cloudflare)
(cf) {
	tls {
		dns cloudflare {env.CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN}
	}
}

